{p} {p}
Objections to the Settlement. At the Settlement Hearing, any
Settlement Class members who has not filed a request for exclusion
from the Settlement Class may appear, in person or by counsel, and be
heard in opposition to: (1) certification of the Settlement Class and
the fairness, reasonableness and adequacy of the Settlement,
including the payment of attorneys' fees and reimbursement of
expenses to Class Counsel; and/or (2) entry of the Judgment;
provided, however, that no objections shall be heard and no papers
submitted by any such objector shall be considered by the Court,
unless, on or before April 21, 1998, such objector: (a) states in
writing the basis for such objections; (b) includes documentary proof
that he, she or it is a member of the Settlement Class; and (c)
provides copies of the foregoing and all other papers in support of
such objections to:
{p} {p}
Plaintiff's and Class Counsel
{p} {p}
Defendants' Counsel
{p} {p}
Circuit Court of Cook County
{p} {p}
IN ORDER TO BE VALID, ALL OBJECTIONS AND PAPERS LISTED ABOVE MUST BE
RECEIVED BY CLASS COUNSEL, DEFENDANTS' COUNSEL AND THE COURT LISTED
ABOVE ON OR BEFORE APRIL 21, 2000.
